            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@ThiefMaster `handle_exception` is not called on `BaseException`s so is not useful. Yes, we use retry middleware to automatically retry transactions which are rolled back due to deadlock. Regardless of whether you consider this good practice, flask should not be treating `BaseException`s as though no error occurred.\r\n\r\n@untitaker My DB driver doesn't raise `SystemExit`, it is raised externally whenever the orchestration system (in this case kubernetes) decides to shutdown a pod. This should be a clean shutdown, and should not be corrupting the database..."
        },
